					<description><![CDATA[<p>Novella, an AI-powered wholesale insurance broker, has raised $21 million in capital to hasten its growth nationwide, hire human brokers, and develop its proprietary AI platform. The round was headed</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/novella-raises-21m-to-scale-ai-insurance-brokerage/" data-wpel-link="internal">Novella Raises $21M to Scale AI Insurance Brokerage</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.bynovella.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Novella</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, an AI-powered wholesale insurance broker, has raised $21 million in </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/mind-robotics-raises-400m/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">capital </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">to hasten its growth nationwide, hire human brokers, and develop its proprietary AI platform.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round was headed by Brewer Lane Ventures. This was also supported by a diverse range of major venture capital players and industry investors such as Box Group, Crystal Venture Partners, SV Angel, Avid Ventures, Verissimo Ventures, Blank Ventures and the world leader in specialty insurance, Arch.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Established in 2024 in New York, this is a startup that operates within the Excess and Surplus (E&amp;S) insurance space. Excess and Surplus Insurance refers to the provision of cover for physical assets of high value or specialty risks that most insurers do not generally underwrite, including towers and skyscrapers in hurricane-prone destinations, large infrastructure projects, and commercial builders&#8217; risk.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">E&amp;S, however, has a far larger market (over $150 billion of premiums each year) and is burdened with a static, legacy process. Conventional brokers can spend as much as half of their working time on manual admin work or reviewing hundreds of pages of policy docs.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Empowering Brokers with Vertical AI</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Novella operates on a hybrid model that pairs human expertise with native, vertical AI agents. Rather than seeking to replace human professionals, the company&#8217;s technology is designed to automate the heavy operational workflows that surround the placement and servicing of specialty insurance.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_201264" style="width: 490px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201264" class="size-full wp-image-201264" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Novella.jpg" alt="Novella logo" width="480" height="92" /><p id="caption-attachment-201264" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Novella</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The proprietary AI platform autonomously manages complex administrative processes. These include initial submission reviews, underwriting appetite matching, form comparison, policy reviews, subjectivity collection, binding, endorsements, inspections, billing, tax filings, and renewals.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By offloading these back-office burdens to AI agents, Novella allows its human producers to dedicate their time entirely to strengthening retail broker relationships and growing their portfolios. The company anticipates that this operational efficiency will enable its brokers to reach individual profitability in half the time required by traditional legacy brokerages.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/mind-robotics-raises-400m/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Mind Robotics Raises $400M To Expand AI Industrial Robotics Platform</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">National Expansion and Accelerated Growth</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The fresh capital injection will support Novella’s aggressive physical and digital expansion strategy. The company is already licensed to operate across all 50 US states and has secured formal appointments from nearly 100 specialty insurance carriers and managing general agents (MGAs), many of which involve limited-distribution agreements.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">On the distribution side, more than 3,500 retail insurance agencies are already appointed and actively routing business through Novella’s platform. The company&#8217;s early client roster features major industry players, including USI and Howden. This rapid commercial adoption allowed Novella to achieve a seven-figure revenue run rate just five months after its initial public launch.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To maintain geographic proximity to its distributed network of retail brokers, Novella is building its physical footprint. The brokerage recently established regional sales offices in Miami, Florida, and Houston, Texas. It plans to open an additional office in Southern California before the end of the second quarter of 2026.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Usage of Funds</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">At the same time, the startup will allocate some of the investment to grow its technical team. Novella itself has 20 employees, about half of whom are based in the company&#8217;s R&amp;D center in Tel Aviv, Israel. The company plans to increase its engineering and developer teams in the R&amp;D center in the coming months in order to keep upgrading its AI platform.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/novella-raises-21m-to-scale-ai-insurance-brokerage/" data-wpel-link="internal">Novella Raises $21M to Scale AI Insurance Brokerage</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
